cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses caching popular content at the edge of future mobile networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on entertainment-oriented content, specifically related video content, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM). The formulation of the problem and analysis of expected gains could also involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of alternative content recommendations on mobile edge caching, which could involve security and privacy (cs.CR) considerations.
